snippet.textDisplay:
This seems to me have been inevitable. From almost day 1 of this season the team hasn't played consistently well and the offense has hardly ever played well at all. You can talk about Brady and how he will be back, but I think the Patriots are already moving on.
They lost the last two games AT HOME to teams they should have and would have beaten in probably any other year.
Tom isn't the quarterback he has been and that is just obvious from most of the games this year. The last two games indicate to me that he isn't the quarterback that they need going forward.
The thrill is gone.
You can be a Pat's fan and still think like a Patriot. The Patriot Way isn't built upon sentimentality. it's built upon results.
These were BAD results. Ugly-bad results.
Changes must and will be made.
